{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"agent_message","text":"# WakeTask iPhone App Spec Candidate (GPT-5 Codex)\n\n## 1) Problem Statement\nPeople who rely on alarms often dismiss or snooze them while half-awake, then miss critical morning commitments. Existing alarm/task apps are either too easy to bypass, too generic, or too punitive.  \n`WakeTask` solves this by requiring meaningful, context-aware completion of a short “wake task” before alarm dismissal is unlocked.\n\n## 2) Target User\n- Primary: working adults and students (18–40) who repeatedly oversleep despite multiple alarms.\n- Secondary: shift workers with strict wake windows and high consequence for lateness.\n- Exclusions for MVP: users seeking medical sleep treatment, pediatric/family parental control use cases.\n\n## 3) MVP Feature Set\n1. Alarm creation/editing\n- One-time and repeating alarms\n- Label, sound, vibration, snooze interval\n\n2. Dismissal gate via wake tasks\n- Task types (MVP): math challenge, sequence memory, short checklist\n- User-configurable difficulty per alarm\n- Alarm can only be dismissed after successful task completion\n\n3. Anti-bypass controls (MVP-safe)\n- Grace window + escalating volume\n- “Snooze quota” per alarm\n- If app is backgrounded during ring, alarm state persists and resumes on foreground\n\n4. Morning focus card\n- After dismissal, show “Next 15 minutes” action card (user-defined micro-task)\n\n5. Basic streak + accountability\n- Daily “on-time wake” tracking\n- Simple streak view (7/30-day)\n\n6. Notifications + reliability\n- Local notifications for alarms\n- Missed-alarm notification with recovery action\n\n7. Onboarding\n- Quick setup wizard: wake goal time, weekdays, preferred task type, fallback snooze policy\n\n## 4) Non-Goals (MVP)\n- Full sleep-cycle analytics or wearable-grade sleep tracking\n- Social competition or public leaderboards\n- AI voice coach/chatbot\n- Calendar auto-scheduling engine\n- Medical claims around sleep disorders\n\n## 5) Core User Journeys\n1. First-run setup\n- User installs app, completes onboarding, creates first weekday alarm with wake task.\n- Success: first alarm scheduled in <2 minutes.\n\n2. Morning alarm flow\n- Alarm rings at scheduled time.\n- User taps dismiss, completes task, sees morning focus card.\n- Success: alarm dismissed only after valid completion.\n\n3. Oversleep recovery\n- User misses alarm or exceeds snooze quota.\n- App shows recovery prompt and allows immediate reschedule for same day.\n- Success: user receives explicit state + one-tap recovery action.\n\n4. Habit reinforcement\n- User checks streak screen and adjusts task difficulty.\n- Success: user can tune challenge without deleting/recreating alarms.\n\n## 6) Acceptance Criteria\n1. Alarm reliability\n- 99%+ successful local alarm trigger rate in internal test matrix across supported iOS versions/devices.\n- Alarm state restoration after app relaunch during active ring.\n\n2. Dismissal gating correctness\n- Dismiss action is blocked until wake task validates.\n- Snooze obeys per-alarm quota and interval settings.\n\n3. UX performance\n- Alarm screen first paint <500ms after foreground.\n- Wake task validation response <100ms perceived for local checks.\n\n4. Data integrity\n- Alarm edits persist across app restarts.\n- Streak counters update deterministically once per wake event.\n\n5. Accessibility\n- Dynamic Type support for primary alarm/task screens.\n- VoiceOver labels on all interactive controls in alarm flow.\n\n## 7) Analytics / Events\n- `onboarding_started`\n- `onboarding_completed`\n- `alarm_created`\n- `alarm_updated`\n- `alarm_triggered`\n- `alarm_snoozed`\n- `alarm_dismiss_attempted`\n- `wake_task_started`\n- `wake_task_completed`\n- `wake_task_failed`\n- `alarm_dismissed`\n- `alarm_missed`\n- `morning_focus_completed`\n- `streak_viewed`\n- `streak_broken`\n- `paywall_viewed` (if monetization is enabled)\n- `subscription_started` (if enabled)\n\nEvent properties:\n- `alarm_id`, `task_type`, `task_difficulty`, `snooze_count`, `time_to_dismiss_sec`, `wake_window_bucket`, `weekday`, `local_tz`\n\n## 8) Privacy / Security Requirements\n- Default local-first storage for alarms and streaks.\n- No collection of contacts/photos/location in MVP.\n- Explicit consent gate before any analytics transmission.\n- PII minimization: no free-text sensitive logging.\n- Encryption at rest for any user identifiers/tokens in Keychain.\n- Privacy Manifest and App Privacy labels aligned with actual SDK data flows.\n- “Delete my data” action for cloud-linked analytics identifier (if cloud analytics enabled).\n\n## 9) App Store 4.3 Differentiation Statement\nWakeTask is not a generic alarm clone. Its core differentiator is **intentional wake verification**: each alarm is tied to configurable cognitive completion gates plus post-dismiss “next-15-minute” execution guidance. The product value is behavior change (reliable wake follow-through), not merely ringing. This creates distinct UX, state logic, and outcomes versus standard alarm/timer templates.\n\n## 10) Appium Exploratory Testing Requirements\n1. Smoke flows\n- First launch → onboarding → create alarm\n- Trigger simulated alarm state → snooze path → dismiss path\n\n2. Failure-path exploration\n- Background/foreground transitions during active alarm\n- Force-close and relaunch while alarm state is pending\n- Invalid wake-task attempts (3+ failures) and recovery UX\n\n3. Device matrix\n- At least 2 iPhone screen classes (compact + large)\n- Current iOS major + previous major\n\n4. Observability\n- Capture screenshots/video for every failed exploratory run\n- Persist Appium logs with step timestamps\n\n5. Exit criteria\n- No P0 blockers in alarm trigger/dismiss flows\n- All known P1 issues have documented workaround or fix plan\n\n## 11) SwiftAIBoilerplatePro Module Reuse Plan\n- `Core`: domain models (`Alarm`, `WakeTask`, `StreakRecord`), business rules, use cases\n- `Storage`: persistence adapters for alarms/streaks/settings\n- `FeatureSettings`: alarm preferences, snooze policy, notification settings\n- `DesignSystem`: alarm ring UI, task cards, streak visuals\n- `Localization`: alarm/task copy + onboarding strings\n- `Networking` (optional in MVP): analytics dispatch abstraction\n- `Auth` / `Payments`: deferred unless gated premium features launch in MVP+1\n- App shell/composition root: wire new `FeatureAlarm` and `FeatureWakeTask` modules with existing dependency injection patterns\n\n## 12) Definition of Done\n- All MVP features implemented and demoable on device.\n- Acceptance criteria pass in CI + local QA checklist.\n- Appium exploratory suite executed with report artifacts.\n- Privacy/security checklist complete (manifest, labels, consent, keychain usage).\n- Crash-free rate baseline established from TestFlight beta.\n- Release notes and known limitations documented.\n- Product, engineering, and QA sign-off recorded.\n\n---\n\nNote: the three specified `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/*` artifacts were not present in this workspace snapshot, so this candidate is written as an independent spec grounded in the stated goal and constraints rather than those missing files directly."}}
